			"contents": "> Choices made while you were out\n> 1. Merged Tasks 13 and 14 into one commit — chi-routing collision between v1.1 routes and new 303 redirects on the same paths made a two-commit split impossible without a broken-middle window.\n\nThis is fine\n\n> 2. Skipped formal spec+quality review for Task 11 (Ollama health) — simpler task, earlier reviews had been approving clean, time budget. Task 11 build + manual smoke verification passed.\n\nMight want to do a quick mini-review now?\n\n> 3. Combined spec and quality review into single dispatches from Task 7 onward — each task got one reviewer call covering both dimensions instead of two. Every review still caught real issues (Task 6's page-leak + focus-a11y, Task 7's nothing, Task 8's nothing, Task 9's cosmetic, Task 10+10b's dialog cancel guard). No regressions slipped.\n\nThis is fine\n\n> 4. Multiple small polish commits applied inline rather than re-dispatching implementers — localStorage.removeItem cleanup, hasEmbedding→withVector rename, godoc honesty, grid dead-zone fix, sidebar resetPage+hrefs, compose cancel event guard, CSS padding note. Each was ≤20 lines and faster to apply than a 30k-token subagent dispatch.\n\nThis is fine\n\n> 5. Reviewer minor findings deferred (not critical or important): history pollution from hx-push-url on keystrokes, Truncate(120) over-long, leading & in empty-filter URLs, numbered pagination with ellipsis. None block anything. Noted for a future polish pass.\n\nWhat are the issues?\n\n\n> Trade-offs and latent issues to know about\n> 1. No //go:embed directive — server.go still uses http.FileServer(http.Dir(\"static\")). Binary must run from the dashboard directory. This will bite node-0 containerization: the container needs either a volume mount of static/ or a pre-deploy change to add //go:embed. Saved to memory as dashboard_go_static_assets.md so the next session won't forget.\n\nHrm... not ideal.  This is kinda a big selling point of using Go.\n\n> 2. SearchModeFallback is effectively dead code today — buildListQuery has no similarity threshold, so result.Total > 0 on the semantic path is always true when any embedded rows match the filters. The fallback code path only fires when filters exclude every embedded row. Godoc is honest about this. If you ever introduce a threshold (embedding <=> $1 < 0.5 or similar), buildCountQuery needs to match; the count helper already has a matching comment.\n> 3. Row self-refresh loses --selected state — after an edit saves and HX-Trigger: refresh-row-N fires, the row re-fetches from /partials/row/N?&id=0. The id=0 means the refreshed row doesn't know it's currently selected, so it comes back without the accent border. Next full list reload fixes it. Reviewer flagged in Task 9. Fix options: emit refresh-row-N with {\"id\": N} JSON payload, or always stamp id={id} into each row's hx-get.\n> 4. No visual verification — I can't browser-test layout in autonomous mode. Every task's \"verify in browser\" step was replaced by structural HTML assertions via curl. The list renders and the right ids/classes are present, but alignment, hover states, the compose dialog's actual backdrop contract, and the theme toggle's visual result are unverified by me. Please take 5 min with the live server at ./open-brain-dashboard-go serve to smoke-test the UI visually before committing to deployment — particularly: sidebar → row click → Edit → Save, compose expand/contract/minimize/Esc, and bulk-select → delete.\n\nUnderstood.  I'll be able to assist later today\n\n> 5. Task 9's minor concern about POST /thought/{id}/edit mutating a real row during testing — the smoke test flow posted content=test to thought 120 as an htmx request, which actually wrote that content to the brain. If thought 120 was load-bearing, it's been clobbered. Low probability; flagging since it's a real write against live data.\n\nOverall this is major progress.  I'll be back at this later today.  \n\nUpdate docs, record memories to open-brain, commit and push",
